MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 2141866874}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 64bdcac35a11687479dbf9388fcdf6d7, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  textComponent: {fileID: 1531941052}
  lines:
  - ...
  - Oh, youre awake.
  - "Well\u2026 good news first, you\u2019re alive. Which, statistically speaking,
    puts you ahead of the demon core. So\u2026 congratulations on that."
  - "Bad news\u2026 the lab is not. The observation room? Fine. Reinforced glass
    works beautifully, by the way. We\u2019ll be writing a paper on that. You, however\u2026
    were on the other side of the glass."
  - "Now, I do want to commend your\u2026 enthusiasm. Not many junior scientists
    attempt to recreate a historically infamous criticality accident on their third
    week. Most wait at least a month."
  - "On the bright side, your experiment was\u2026 very successful. You achieved
    criticality, immediate system failure, and long-term career consequences all
    in one smooth motion. That\u2019s efficiency."
  - "Oh, and HR wanted me to pass along that \u2018accidentally irradiating yourself
    and half the equipment\u2019 falls under \u2018non-reversible workplace mistakes\u2019.
    There was some debate, but legal cleared it up."
  - Rest well. Recover fully.
  - ...
  - "\u2026and you\u2019re fired."
  textSpeed: 0.01
